In this article, President Barack Obama proclaims May 2014 as National Physical Fitness and Sports Month. He emphasizes the importance of sports in keeping children healthy, teaching teamwork, and developing discipline. He mentions the Let's Move! initiative led by First Lady Michelle Obama, which aims to promote a healthy lifestyle for children and empower schools to create active environments. The Presidential Youth Fitness Program and the Presidential Active Lifestyle Award are also mentioned as efforts to prioritize students' health and encourage all Americans to eat right and exercise regularly. The President's Council on Fitness, Sports, and Nutrition is expanding a program called I Can Do It, You Can Do It! to provide more opportunities for Americans with disabilities to participate in fitness and sports. President Obama calls upon the people of the United States to prioritize daily physical activity, sports participation, and good nutrition in their lives.